N O  S E C R E T
We’ve made one of our bedtime stories around his adoption. On this night, a couple years ago, he shared his story w me instead. It’s a slow tale, but so cute. #adoption #openadoptions

T O P P E D 
Well, we did it!! The tree is “trimmed” and topped, as some us might say. Ha! Our traditional photo of me hoisting @atorable12 up is becoming more challenging as he grows.

S M I L E
We are almost through yet another year.
I try to focus on what I’m thankful for and I try to not let the difficult times overshadow all the good that surrounds. 
My baby is transforming into a young man before my eyes (I know every parent has experienced this as well). I’m grateful for the compassion and empathy I see in his heart. I’m even more grateful for his healthy sense of self and learning boundaries at this young age. I can’t imagine how different I’d have been had my parents known how to show me about those. 

Smile. Give a hug to someone you love. Reach out to someone you might not often speak to. Holidays can have their challenges for each of us. 

Lots of love.  From Torb and I.

A V A T A R
like many we put on some funny glasses and watched avatar in 3-D, but also 4Dx. 
I really liked it. I thought it played into its original theme nicely while giving new storyline. 
I think these designers of the  4D soundtracks need a reality check. The thrashing around of the seats is way over done and the volume needs to come down at least 20 to 40%. Previously, I had watched top gun in 4D and I felt the same. I went to avatar, hoping James Cameron had a better handle on this.  And with a three hour movie it’s just exhausting. 
** my 10 year old son, thought it was even too much and got out of his seat and sat on the floor!!! 

@avatar @jamescameronofficial @regalmovies @topgunmovie

S A T U R D A Y
It’s so cozy in here. A cocoon of sorts. A place to just breathe for a moment.

B O U N D R I E S
I never understood boundaries when I was little. My wonderful mother just didn’t understand them herself, muchless to teach them to her children. 
As an adult, post divorce, and 1000s of hours of therapy - I finally understand boundaries and their invaluable application in our daily lives. And now … I get to give my kiddo a head start and teaching him the  gift of boundaries. For himself, and for those he comes into contact with on his long journey of life. 

And yes. The skiing was EPICCCCCCCC

V I C A R I O U S L Y
My office for the day. A beautiful beach house in Malibu - the views from every room in the place are pretty endless… I’m grateful to have this opportunity to work on this project and I sure can’t wait to share more about it. 

I live vicariously through some of my clients. Many people live vicariously through the SM feeds to which we subscribe. But it’s important to simply find the serenity and gratitude for where we are….
Happiness is most definitely from within our own. Don’t lose sight of that ;)

R E F R E S H
Sometimes it’s the little things. About 20min ago my desktop on my computer had a 1000 files cluttered upon it. Now, just a few remain. 
Sometimes we just need a defrag. Ha. There’s an old PC term!! Who remembers it??

Weekend is upon us! Now to get upon someone or something!

Work work work.

A N G E L S
Well, that day has come where I have no more living grandparents. Yesterday, my dear gma departed. 

Even as young as kindergarten I knew how fortunate I was to have not just one of my grandparents alive, but all four. I even had three of my great-grandparents! 
I’m truly grateful that @atorable12 was able to know and meet these two though… because sadly, I don’t think we make people like this (very often) anymore. 

My grandmother was strong and independent. She didn’t take no for an answer and she stood by her word. She built a successful business selling cars - at a time women were expected to run the household.
I could tell you stories for hours about her, and my grandpa. Two of the best human beings I have ever met. 

Her story in coming to america during the war is awe-inspiring. 
Her wisdom far transcended anything I could comprehend as a young boy. Even still today, she inspires my parenting, my business, my integrity. 

She’ll be home again w my mom and grandpa. Her husband of 70yrs, this Sunday. 

I won’t say that there’s a hole in my heart, but instead that my heart is whole. She lived a full and beautiful life. She would only probably regret that she couldn’t have traded her life for my mom’s…. 10yrs ago.

We say farwell to her here on earth and grandpa gets his angel back by his side. 🪽 #angels #death #family #grandma #love

F R I Y A Y

D A D
It’s a symbiotic relationship. 
He makes me laugh. I may him laugh. 
He frustrates the crud outta me(sometimes), and do the same to him (when he’s playing on his VR). 
Dads are just born big brothers in a lot of ways. 
I love being dad (and a lot of times mom). I’m grateful he gets to know his birth mom. I know it means a lot to him. 

I dated this guy once who was in process of adoption or surrogacy, I don’t recall atm. When I asked him “why do you wanna be a parent” he literally couldn’t reply. Had no answer (and this was a true wordsmith). 
My interest in him deflated in that moment. It’s almost like the kid was something he could afford, gave him legacy… I still don’t know. But his uncertainty ended our dating - because my answer to that question is simple. I want to be a dad. I want to share in his life. I want to see the joy on his face and I want to hold him when life’s lessons come a knockin’. 

Anyway. Just thought I’d share a totally precious picture  pre-father’s day stuff. ;)
Just. Be.

L I F E

I figured I better get this winter post out as summer is almost upon us. So much about this photo brings me joy. My little one is growing up right before my eyes. Turning into quite a young man. And I get stopped in my tracks every once in a while when I see how much like my dad, sometimes. 

#Dad #FamilyPhotos #GrowingBoys #gaydad #openadoption

P R I D E

1/ TRANSPARENT The Musical
PLEASE go and support this show. It’s such an important and relevant topic on all levels (Florida/nazi germany). Thank you @ctgla for making a wonderful kick off to Pride Month. 
2/ thank you to my city, LA, for being a beautiful melting pot, a shining example of tolerance and love, and for wearing OUR PRIDE right on City Hall for all to share. 
3/ thank you to my friend @jtownla for being my theater buddy and friend. (He wanted to be as tall as me, thus the shot where I’m not towering over him. Ha)

It’s pride month and our country, our world, is seeing a lot of horribleness that we thought was only true in the history books. Be as KIND and GENEROUS as possible. Let’s prove that compassion is stronger than H8 and that we can all live on this blue planet together.  #Kumbaya
#Pride #CityOfAngels #Rainbow #Love #Peace #noh8

P R I D E  A F
I do my best to wear my pride gleefully and honorably. I am proud to have been part of the movement to bring us to where we are today. Sadly, we see that the goal keeps being moved by those w a more heinous and devious agenda, often under a “religious” cloak. 
We have more allies than ever. We are an amazing group when united together. 

Make love not war, and sparkle w all your might. It’s exactly what Jesus did.

CH-CH-CHANGES
One year ago yesterday I was sitting in the chair to add some LONG-AWAITED ink. For years I had waited for @gilleslovisa to make it back to SoCal. After ~16yrs I simply couldn’t wait any longer. I was FORCED to head back to Tahiti!!!

I LOVE MY INK. 
Every day I look at it and smile.
I think of my magical adventure and the friend who was so instrumental in the story. 
Getting a full sleeve, muchless a full back and chest tattooed, gets a whole different reaction from people than what I had experienced before. One of the biggest differences I hear is the FEAR people have around the permanence and regretting their decision. I say to them “I love my tatts and the memories attached to them. I thought long and hard about the style and the content of them. Luckily I had already met the most amazing artist - so all I had to do was show up and endure that needle for 9days (almost 46hrs).”

Do you have a tattoo that you regret?
Do you have one that you LOVE?

#yolo #tattoodad #polynesiantattoo #mauritattoo #tahiti #moorea #gaytravel #interiordesign #dznrdadventures #loveyourself

S T O P
Even if only for a brief moment today, I took some solo time to breathe, float, and listen to some great music in the pool. 
One must STOP on occasion and just take life in. I’m not always good at this. I’ve always been a mover and doer… so. There ya have it.

75  D E G R E E S

Summer was kinda short this year in SoCal. Didn’t really get warmed until July and by end of August, we were seeing those temps fall again. This has been one of the most beautiful Septembers I think I’ve ever experienced here. I love it. 

Pool temp is dropping but it didn’t stop me from taking a dip. Skinny-style, if ya care. What a beautiful day. 

#pools #summerlovin #saturdayvibes #gaydad

F L A M E

My flame burns stronger than ever today. I know and trust more of myself than ever before. It would be fun to have known this person in my 20s, but at least I met him as I turned 40. 
I know this is true for many of us. It takes time to learn and grow and trust…

Be good to yourself. Be patient. Keep the movement forward.

H O L Y  C O W E L L
An hour before taping was to begin for the @agt #agtfinalle a friend called (who works on the show) and said he had a couple tickets available for the taping…. and could we get to Pasadena (in ~ 50min). Well, we were in full swing w back-to-school night and I had leap into action if we were going to make it home, change our clothes and get to Pasadena (through rush-hour, nevertheless), get parked and to our seats in time. 
Clearly, we made it. We had awesome seats in the orchestra and the energy in that auditorium was something to be experienced!! At the end of the show the spectacle landed on stage w the winner @adrianstoica.dogcoach and the rest of the AGT team, participants and press. Long story short, after the main exodus of audience, the auditorium was winding down - the @simoncowell managed to shake hands and a few words w @atorable12 , a young admirer, before heading back stage. 
It was an LA moment to say the least. 
** The universe gives us these little treasures. I think in modern life we have come to expect them… (and pretty often). I try to impress upon the kiddo that these are lil gifts, to take a breath and really be present when they’re happening. 
I loved seeing the smiles on his face throughout the evening… and the days that followed. 

Thank you to my awesome friend for an incredible evening. We didn’t get to spend time w @howiemandel like Torb wanted, but there’s always next season. 
.
.
#bucketlist #television #goldenbuzzer #talent #hollywood #pasadena #singledad

B I R T H D A Y 
I tried to grab only a few photos to share here, but how does one just narrow it down to ten or so? So, I did not. I made a video and now y’all can indulge me for 4min. ;). 

So many memories. So much to be grateful for.
It has taken the majority of my 40-something years to live the love I am living. The phrase “living my best life” has been ringing in my ears lately. Not because I really love the phrase, but in so many ways I feel it from within. 
I’ve hand selected the 88 or so pics and videos in this slideshow, most of them from this last 365days. 
My son, my friends…. And tribute to my grandparents (I lost my last living grandmother earlier this year) and of course my most-amazing mother. I sure hope she sees what all that hard work has done and knows how very much she is missed and loved, despite not being here beside me in the flesh. 
To my friends: you know who you are and how much I value and love you in my life. Some of us don’t see one another often. Some, maybe too much. Ha! But truly, you add so much to my life and I probably don’t say it often enough to you. 
To my son: may you find your sparkle early and never let ANYONE diminish its strength. You bring me every joy that I can hope I brought to my mother… and father. 
To a man who’s come into my life and given me so many of the things I’ve only dreamt about. May the dream continue and expand into everything it can possibly be. 
And to my future friends…. may you find some sparkle in my zaniness and use it for good in your own superhero journey….
Thank you for your time and love and wishes. 
Spread your sparkle as a gift to me. The world needs it, now and always. 

#birthday #gaydad #40something #tattoodad #inkeddaddy #loveinallforms
